# Normalize line endings. Text files are LF in the repo AND on checkout —
# `eol=lf` overrides a contributor's `core.autocrlf`, so Windows/WSL stop
# fighting and the "LF will be replaced by CRLF" warnings disappear for good.
# Git auto-detects text vs binary; the explicit `binary` lines below are
# belt-and-suspenders so raster assets are never line-ending-touched or
# text-diffed. The index is already pure-LF, so adding this file is a
# zero-content-change normalization (verified via `git add --renormalize`).
* text=auto eol=lf

# Raster icon assets (Tauri scaffold) — never treat as text.
*.png  binary
*.ico  binary
*.icns binary

# SVG is XML/text — keep it LF (the default covers it; explicit for clarity).
*.svg  text eol=lf

# Committed lockfiles: LF text, but collapse them in PR diffs and exclude
# them from GitHub's language stats (generated, not authored).
Cargo.lock  text eol=lf linguist-generated=true
bun.lock    text eol=lf linguist-generated=true
